Airiti Library華藝線上圖書館





































													篇名
												


兩岸產品責任制度之比較研究






														並列篇名
													


															Comparison on the Law of Products Liability across the Taiwan Straits
														




														作者
													


															李秀梅

														




													關鍵字
												



														懲罰性賠償 ； 產品責任 ； 產品質量 ； 產品瑕疵 ； 兩岸消保法 ； punitive compensation ； laws on consumer protection across the Taiwan St ； defect products ； products liability ； products quality and quantity
													




													出版品名稱
												


														成功大學法律學系學位論文
													




													捲期/出版年月
												


碩士													




														學位類別
													

碩士




														指導教授
													

郭麗珍




													內容語文
												

繁體中文




														中文摘要
													

產業經濟的變革導致消費時代的改變，現代社會中商品大量生產、銷售通路廣泛多元，使得產品的複雜性與危險性攀升，消費者在享受科技便利成果的同時，亦承擔因瑕疵商品造成不當損害之風險。不肖廠商為求暴利而生產、經銷的產品，致令專業資訊不足之消費者在錯誤判斷下消費，進而導致生命、身體、財產等基本權利遭受嚴重侵害的事件，在世界各國時有所聞。然而，各國為因應國內消費者保護浪潮，紛紛制訂相關商品責任法制，以保護弱勢消費者的合法權益。揆諸世界各國消費趨勢的變化，產品安全的確保將是本世紀經濟發展的必然商業趨勢。而台灣與大陸同在亞洲經濟圈內，基於時空距離與文化語言的無隔閡，近年來兩岸商業互動頻繁、商品互通有無，故而兩岸產品責任法制之異同與完善與否，關係兩岸消費者權益甚鉅。本論文試比較研析兩岸現行商品責任法制之異同與優劣缺失，以期對兩岸人民消費智識的提升、消費權益的維護略盡棉薄之力。




														英文摘要
													

The revolution in industrial economy has led to changes in modern day consumption. Products are massively produced and sold extensively. The result is a rise in the complexity and danger of product liability. While consumers enjoy the advantages of technology, they are also at risk of suffering damages from defective products. We've heard worldwide that flawed manufactured products are produced in order to make huge and sudden profits. A consumer who lacks professional knowledge and judgment will have his body, life, property and other rights violated when using these defective products. As a countermeasure, many countries have constituted laws related to product liability, in order to protect the consumer's legal rights.
The insurance of product safety is certain to be a business trend in the economical development of this century, according to global consumptive trends.  Taiwan and the People's Republic of China are in the same economical range in Asia, due to frequent business interactions in recent years. Thus the differences and the completeness of the products liability laws across the Taiwan Straits will have huge influences on the rights of the consumers. 
This paper will set out to compare and analyze the differences, advantages, and disadvantages on the law of product liability across the Taiwan Straits, and looks forward to conduce the enhancement of people's consumptive knowledge and rights across the Taiwan Straits.




													主題分類
													

社會科學院													> 
法律學系													
社會科學													> 
法律學													




